item.title: [HIVE-23551] Acid: Update queries should treat dirCache as read-only in AcidUtils
item.description: Update statements create delta folders at the end of the execution. When insert overwrite followed by update is executed, it does not get any open txns and ends up caching the base folder. However, the delta folder which gets created at the end of the statement never makes it to the cache. This creates wrong results.
item.summary: Acid: Update queries should treat dirCache as read-only in AcidUtils

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.
